Afropolitan: A Digital Nation - Manifesto Citizen Manifesto Community Events Podcast Newsletter Introducing Afropolitan: A Digital Nation What is Afropolitan? Afropolitan is creating a Digital Nation to enable all Africans to build abundant We are building a network comprising the best that Africa and the diaspora offer across art, finance, tech, health, energy, sports, and The Afropolitan Network is a Curator of Black and African: Talent (recruit, partner up) Culture (art, media, fashion) Capital (investment DAOs) Information (newsletter, blog, Twitter) Experiences (events, curated offerings) Nevertheless, we believe our reach should exceed our While it may be a humble Network today, Afropolitan will be the internet country in the But we√¢¬Ä¬ôre getting ahead of First, you may be asking: why build a Digital Nation? Why we√¢¬Ä¬ôre building a Digital Nation Each generation must, out of relative obscurity, discover its mission, fulfill it, or betray √¢¬Ä¬î Frantz Fanon Wherever we look and wherever we are, Africans worldwide are subjects, not Access to opportunity is Security is not For the most part, life is just about surviving, not What would you do if you could do anything? If your future was boundless, not bounded ? What if your allegiance to a country did not depend on birth but on choice? In short: What would happen if you could come together with others to build a new society? We know what you√¢¬Ä¬ôre thinking: √¢¬Ä¬úThis is unrealistic ¬Ä¬ù Everything around you, from the machine on which you√¢¬Ä¬ôre reading this manifesto to the country you live in, was once an idea in somebody√¢¬Ä¬ôs They only came to be thanks to the work of millions of people, no more intelligent or better than In this spirit, and with humility and hope for the future, we Afropolitans declare: The experiment has failed for Black people It has yielded nothing but poverty, genocide, police brutality, ethnic strife, inflation, weak government, and the failure of our All people who call themselves free have a fundamental right to create the society they want by choice As the internet enables us to shrink space and form bonds across the planet, no person should live in a society by accident or Finally, that Abundance and the destruction of scarcity is a North Star worth pursuing in any society which hopes to be both healthy and Instead of the Land of Opportunity, we propose the Network of Abundance : Abundance of Tools , Abundance of Opportunity , Abundance of Joy . To all future Afropolitans, our deal is simply this: join the Network of Abundance to be all you can Afropolitan is the canvas you wield the Strategy: How do you build a Digital Nation? Human beings are social All that is good and noble about us stems from the fact that we need each In the most basic sense, building a new country is a process of scaling a social network around a shared mission and Social networks are formed online and tend to stay there in our But what if we built a new network and migrated it into the real world via a city (or Network of cities)? Balaji Srinivasan highlighted this as the most viable strategy to build such a country √¢¬Ä¬î which he calls a Network State √¢¬Ä¬î in the The Network State is a digital nation launched first as an online community before materializing physically on land after reaching critical The internet enables people to organize around shared values at scales that were previously unthinkable before the current If it were a country, Facebook would be the largest one With the advent of cryptocurrency, the next Facebook will not be a social network with a passive online community but rather a digital republic coordinated by its native currency and a unifying What, then, could Afropolitan be? If it were a country, the African diaspora would be the largest globally (~ Million). The diaspora is our North Master Plan The best way to reform an obsolete system is by building a newer, more straightforward Afropolitan√¢¬Ä¬ôs objective is to solve the Crisis of Legitimacy experienced by Africans worldwide by building a new source of Legitimacy embodied in our Digital Nation . We will do so in four phases: Phase 1: Network In the first phase of our plan, we will focus on building awareness and excitement about the Afropolitan Network and the digital nation we are We will do this by launching an NFT (non-fungible token) campaign that will outline the mythology and vision for our new Afropolitan NFTs will also grant members access to exclusive events and future services, as well as a digital passport that will allow them to participate in the Our goal is to seed the network with passionate and engaged members who are committed to building a better world for Phase 2: Come for the Network, Stay for the Tool In the second phase of our plan, we will focus on providing our members with maximum value and utility through the Afropolitan Super This app will bring together all the different utilities and services within the Afropolitan ecosystem in one place, allowing members to

rhizomatiq rhizomatiq transparent dlt utilities for the cannabis supply chain what is rhizomatiq? rhizomatiq is a distributed ledger technology [dlt] that utilizes a distributed acyclic graph [dag] consensus a dag is a distributed ledger, based on account chains called "nodes", which can SEND or RECEIVE tansactions, referred to as "seeds". the authorization process for approving seeds to the node is easy and efficient, all done by the account owner meaning no built on top of this dlt is a suite of transparent supply chain utilities our track trace mechanism, which follows relationships of items, our document reader, which allows companies to batch upload supply chain documentation for conversion into usable data, and much these utilities track shipments, batches, and products across the chain to give participants a broader understanding of the activities behind the rhizomatiq has two main goals the first is to make the cannabis industry more in CO & CA, our launch states, there is little to no transparency as to where the cannabis that you ingest actually comes full lab results are unavailable, you are unable to view the history of the product s storage and maintenence, or sometimes just know where the product was originally the second is to open up mobile payments in even with the incredibly strict rules and regulations around entry to cannabis establishments in most states, there is still an incredible lack in efficient payment you re stuck with cash, or a PoS payments solution that acts like an ATM, and therefore charges outrageous fees on top of the cannabis excise and sales rhizomatiq offers a c2m solution named "Sqan", a mobile payment platform that offers the ability to pay for cannabis in seconds with a flat fee of only $1 rhizomatiq also offers a more sophisticated s2m solution, with a tiered pricing model capped at % Tx which moves down according to what is a directed acyclic graph? this is a directed acyclic it is a mathematical graphing concept, to represent relationships between it has been adapted into computer science as a database principle these relationships represent data points that connect the two parties, and this representation method allows for incredibly simple storage of transactional on rhizomatiq, transactions representing data tie accounts together, weaving together a story of how products have come down the supply the technical basis behind this is that when a pair SEND RECEIVE transaction is generated, one of these dag relational transactions is also authentication is done locally, by each individual account tangle (node) approving the transactions they were responsible for sending so, if you sent the SEND transaction, you will verify that SEND on your chain, while the person who sent the RECEIVE will approve the corresponding RECEIVE this adds both transactions to their corresponding chain and approves the transaction utilizing the attached supply chain services will give you full access into the important supply chain this is a simplified diagram of a set of account unlike a blockchain, the SEND is stored with the sender, and the RECEIVE is stored with the this makes the process incredibly efficient and scalable you don t need lots of independent verifiers authorizing transactions, each participating party on the chain does all rights reserved rhizomatiq, llc
